    <description>The Ocean Optics UV-Flame is located at the Planetary Geosciences Laboratory at the Planetary Science Institute in Tucson, AZ. It is a portable, compact spectrometer designed to measure light across ultraviolet (UV) and visible wavelengths, typically ranging from 200 to 850 nm. It is commonly used for flame spectroscopy applications, where it analyzes the light emitted by flames to identify chemical elements and their concentrations. This spectrometer is equipped with a high-sensitivity detector and can be connected to a computer for data analysis and visualization. It's widely used in research, industrial, and environmental settings to monitor combustion processes or perform chemical analysis.                </description>
